Reasoning: The paper deals with undecidability and complexity results for recognition of languages of infinite pictures by tiling systems, which is a topic in formal language theory and computability theory. The use of logical hierarchies and automata models also suggests connections to logic and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
